      • find

        protected IPosition<T> find​(IPosition<T> start,
                            T value)
        Find a node in the tree that contains a particular value.
        Parameters:
        start - The node to begin the search from (to search an entire tree, begin at its root).
        value - The value to search for.
        Returns:
        The internal node that contains value, if it is contained in the tree. If value is not contained in the tree, returns the external node that the search terminated at.
